==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Purpresture
<hw>Pur*pres"ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably
corrupted (see <er>Prest</er>) fr. OF. <ets>pourprisure</ets>, fr.
<ets>pourprendre</ets>: cf. LL. <ets>purprestura</ets>. Cf.
<er>Purprise</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Wrongful encroachment
upon another's property; esp., any encroachment upon, or inclosure of,
that which should be common or public, as highways, rivers, harbors,
forts, etc.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>pourpresture</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purprise</ent>⟦br⟧
